        <div class="slide-content">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-800">Early Life & The Laws of Thought</h2>
            <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 items-center">
                <div class="md:w-1/2">
                    <p class="text-gray-700">Born in Lincoln, England, George Boole's story is one of a self-taught genius. Despite a humble background and limited formal education, he demonstrated remarkable intellectual curiosity. By the age of 16, he was working as a teacher to support his family, all while independently studying Latin, Greek, and advanced mathematics.</p>
                    <p class="text-gray-700 mt-4">His passion and talent led him to a professorship at Queen's College, Cork, even without a university degree. It was here that he produced his most famous work, <strong>"An Investigation of the Laws of Thought"</strong> (1854), which outlined the principles of what we now call Boolean algebra.</p>
                    <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AY1NDlKlPp4" target="_blank" class="nav-button bg-red-600 text-white mt-4 inline-flex">
