    <!-- Slide 3: Major Contributions -->
    <div id="slide3" class="slide">
        <div class="slide-content">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-800">Boolean Algebra: The Foundation</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Boole's masterpiece introduced a new system of logic that uses algebraic symbols to represent logical propositions. Instead of numbers, his algebra dealt with two values: <strong>true (1)</strong> and <strong>false (0)</strong>. He established three core operations: <strong>AND</strong>, <strong>OR</strong>, and <strong>NOT</strong>.</p>
            <div class="flex justify-center">
                <img src="https://placehold.co/600x300/475569/FFFFFF?text=Boolean+Logic+Gates" alt="Diagram of logic gates" class="rounded-xl shadow-lg">
            </div>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mt-4">This elegant system could be used to solve complex logical problems and was a radical departure from traditional Aristotelian logic. While he never saw its full potential, Boole created the mathematical framework that would one day power every digital circuit and computer.</p>
            <a href="https://www.codecademy.com/resources/blog/what-is-boolean-logic" target="_blank" class="nav-button bg-blue-600 text-white mt-4 inline-flex">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
                    <path d="M10 12a2 2 0 100-4 2 2 0 000 4z" />
                    <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm0 2a10 10 0 100-20 10 10 0 000 20z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
                </svg>
                Learn More about Boolean Logic
            </a>
        </div>
        <div class="navigation-buttons">
            <button id="prevBtn3" class="nav-button bg-gray-200 text-gray-800">
